data.text:
Tonight in L.A.: The Breeders, Nina Diaz/Prima Donna, Brasstracks, Autograf, Story of the Year, Crowder, Vera Sola, Janelle Kroll, T.S.O.L., Arlo Guthrie, Low Cut Connie, Brenda Carsey, Kongos, Wallows, Guana Batz, Yellow Days, State to State

L.A. concerts for Thursday:

► The Breeders play the first of three SoCal shows in support of their new album “All Nerve,” tonight at the Fonda Theatre. Cherry Glazerr opens.

► Chicago’s Autograf headlines the El Rey Theatre, supported by Wine & Woo and Cofresi.

► Horns-synths-and-drums duo Brasstracks light up the Roxy, with S’natra opening.

► With her solo album still garnering acclaim, Nina Diaz headlines the Hi Hat. Also on board, L.A. rockers Prima Donna, celebrating the release of their new album “S/T,” and Wild Moccasins.

► Vera Sola, a multi-instrumentalist/singer-songwriter/composer who has toured with the likes of Elvis Perkins, headlines the Bootleg Theater in support of her forthcoming album “Shades.” Hush Arbors supports.

► And singer-songwriter Janelle Kroll visits the Satellite, joined by FYOHNA and Dolly Spectra.
